crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist, Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: A graceful evergreen shrub (family Myrtaceae) with linear terete leaves and loose lateral clusters of reddish flowers; native to Australia. Previous introduction referenced: 77277.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist, Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: An undershrub (family Proteaceae) with usually simple stems 1 to 2 feet high and petioled basal leaves with nearly orbicular blades about 1 inch long. The stem leaves are bractlike, closely appressed, and only about half an inch long. Flexuose spikes, 2 to 3 inches long, arise in the axils of the upper leaves and bear small white or violet flowers densely covered with silky white hairs; native to Western Australia. Previous introduction referenced: 93835.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist, Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: A tall shrub (family Malvaceae), native to Australia, with 3- to 5-lobed, coarsely toothed leaves 1 to 3 inches long and large violet-purple flowers. Previous introduction referenced: 95327.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist, Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: A low spiny evergreen shrub (family Myrtaceae) with very small lanceolate leaves about one-fourth inch long and small solitary axillary white flowers; native to southwestern Australia.

crops.presented_by: C. A. Gardner, Government Botanist, Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.institution_involved: Department of Agriculture, Perth, Western Australia
crops.description: A low shrub (family Myrtaceae) with opposite fleshy semiterete leaves crowded at the ends of the branches and small purplish flowers in the leaf axils.

crops.presented_by: F. H. Baker, Richmond, Victoria
crops.description: An Australian tree up to 300 feet high, with lanceolate leaves about 4 inches long, crowded umbels of small flowers, and hemispheric fruits about one-fourth inch broad. The leaves have a strong peppermint odor and are rich in oil. Previous introduction referenced: 93228.

crops.presented_by: F. H. Baker, Richmond, Victoria
crops.description: Variety Rosea, a pink-flowered form of Eucalyptus calophylla.

crops.presented_by: F. H. Baker, Richmond, Victoria
crops.description: A medium-sized evergreen tree, native to Australia, with leathery lanceolate leaves and large corymbs of fragrant yellowish-white flowers.
